My husband jokingly said, “You break it, you bought it.” I think this scared her. She went into my daughter's room and hid under a blanket. She cried for a long time. Because I was out taking another child home, I was not home when it happened. I texted the child's father (our neighbor across the street) to tell him she accidentally broke the iPad and that she was inconsolable.
